threat_severity.level_description: Severity MEDIUM because it was considered trojan.

attributes.magic: ELF 32-bit MSB executable, MIPS, MIPS-I version 1 (SYSV), statically linked, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: The sample is a DDoS botnet agent, likely a variant of Bashlite (Gafgyt) or Mirai, targeting MIPS-based Linux IoT devices. It demonstrates several malicious behaviors: 1) Anti-analysis/Anti-VM checks by querying '/sys/class/dmi/id/product_name' for 'VMware' (sub_400960). 2) Process enumeration and termination of competing processes or security tools by scanning '/proc' and comparing against a whitelist (sub_4026e4). 3) Multiple DDoS attack modules supporting SYN, ACK, UDP, ICMP, and GRE floods, as well as an HTTP flood module (sub_406ea4) using hardcoded User-Agents. 4) C2 command handling for attack triggers like '!syn', '!ack', and '!http' (sub_40559c). 5) Single-instance execution enforcement via a lock file at '/tmp/.bot_lock'.
